This has led to a number of teams expressing their needs in the upcoming January transfer window. Meanwhile, the league has ended its 20-year partnership with IMG, which will see the league take over media production operations. The league has also made changes to its associated party transaction rules and the APT rules following the Manchester City case. The Premier League has also confirmed the dates for the 2025/26 season and has approved changes to the squad number rule, allowing teams to field XIs using only numbers 1-11.

name: JFK
summary: Despite having promised their release, President Trump has yet to release the remaining files on the assassination of President John F. Kennedy, 61 years after the event. The assassination remains a subject of fascination and speculation, with new details emerging periodically. Experts caution against expecting major revelations from the release of the files, as they may not contain any earth-shattering information. Nevertheless, the files are anticipated to provide additional insights into the events surrounding the assassination and its aftermath, as well as the impact it had on individuals and institutions, including President Trump himself.

name: Scott Turner
summary: President Trump has nominated Scott Turner, a former Republican state representative from Texas, to head the Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD). Turner, who played cornerback for the Dallas Cowboys during his NFL career, has been a White House aide since 2017. Despite a lack of experience in housing policy, Trump has praised Turner's "tremendous leadership" and ability to "get things done." The appointment has drawn criticism from some experts, who argue that Turner is unqualified to lead HUD, which has a budget of over $40 billion and oversees programs for affordable housing, community development, and homelessness.
